Telugu (English letters lo explanation)

Framework ante oka automation project ki backbone laga untundi. Idi manam code ela rayali, ela organize cheyyali, ela run cheyyali, results ela chudali ani define chestundi. Python Playwright + Pytest framework lo manam real-time ga use chese structure chala systematic ga untundi, idi team lo andariki same understanding istundi.

Ippudu full structure ni story laga ardham chesukundam. Meeru oka automation project start chesaru anukondi. First ga tests/ ane folder untundi. Ikkada actual test cases untayi, ante user flow ni simulate chese scripts. Example: login test, payment test. Ee tests lo direct ga locators petti code rayakudadhu, maintainability kosam separate ga petali.

Next pages/ (POM layer). Ikkada prathi web page ki oka class untundi. Example: LoginPage, DashboardPage. Ikkada locators + actions (click, enter text) untayi. Idi maintainability ki chala important. UI change ayithe ikkade change chesthe saripothundi.

Next utils/ or common/. Ikkada reusable functions untayi. Example: API calls, database connection, date handling, random data generation. Okkasari rasina functions ni multiple tests lo reuse chestam.

Next config/. Ikkada environment details untayi. Example: base URL, credentials, browser type. Usually .env or config.yaml lo maintain chestam. Dev, QA, Prod environments ni easy ga switch cheyyochu.

Next conftest.py (Hooks). Idi pytest lo chala important file. Ikkada setup and teardown logic untundi. Example: browser launch, page open, close browser. Fixtures ikkade define chestam. Idi global control center laga untundi.

Next test_data/. Ikkada input data untundi (JSON/Excel). Data Driven testing kosam use chestam. Same test ni different data tho run cheyyachu.

Next reports/. Execution tarvata reports generate avutayi. Pytest-html or Allure use chestam. Ikkada pass/fail status, logs, screenshots untayi.

Next logs/. Debugging kosam logs maintain chestam. Failure ekkada jarigindo easy ga telustundi.

Next screenshots/. Test fail ayithe automatic ga screenshot capture ayi ikkada save avutundi. Evidence laga use avutundi.

Next cookies/session handling. Konni projects lo login skip cheyyadaniki cookies save/load chestam. Time save avutundi.

Next pytest.ini. Ikkada pytest configurations untayi. Example: markers, default options.

Next requirements.txt. Project ki kavalsina dependencies list untundi (playwright, pytest etc.).

Flow ela untundi ante: Test file → Page class ni call chestundi → Page class UI actions perform chestundi → Utils/common functions support chestayi → conftest fixtures browser ni manage chestayi → Execution tarvata reports + screenshots generate avutayi.

Real-time lo idi complete cycle.

Interview lo strong answer: Python Playwright framework with pytest follows POM structure with separate layers like tests, pages, utils, config, and fixtures. It supports data-driven testing, reusable functions, reporting, logging, and screenshot capture, making the framework scalable and maintainable.

English (Simple Explanation)

A framework is the structured setup of an automation project. It defines how code is organized, executed, and maintained.

In a Python Playwright + Pytest framework, the structure is usually like this:

tests/ → Contains test cases (actual scenarios)
pages/ → Page Object Model (each page has locators and methods)
utils/common/ → Reusable functions (API calls, helpers)
config/ → Environment details (URL, credentials)
conftest.py → Pytest hooks and fixtures (setup/teardown, browser handling)
test_data/ → Input data (JSON/Excel for data-driven testing)
reports/ → HTML or Allure reports
logs/ → Execution logs for debugging
screenshots/ → Captured on failure
cookies/session → Used to manage login sessions
pytest.ini → Pytest configuration
requirements.txt → Dependencies

Execution flow:
Test → Calls Page → Page interacts with UI → Utils support → Fixtures manage browser → Reports & screenshots generated

Interview answer:
“A Playwright Python framework with pytest is structured using POM. It includes test scripts, page classes, reusable utilities, configuration files, and pytest fixtures. It supports reporting, logging, screenshots, and data-driven testing, making it scalable and maintainable.” 🚀
